5. Legal reasons and collection method of your personal data
We collect your personal data by automatic and non-automatic methods through the DeepWall panel (API) and website.
We will only collect and use your personal data (as described in section 4) in accordance with relevant data protection laws.  Our legal grounds for processing your personal data are as follows:
1. Consent
- Where necessary we will only collect and process your personal data if you have given your clear and affirmative consent for us to do so. In order to promote DeepWall and carry out marketing activities, your contact information is processed in order to contact you via e-mail if we have your express consent. You may withdraw your consent anytime without any reason by sending an e-mail to info@deepwall.com .
2. Legitimate Interests
- We may use and process some of your personal data where we have sensible and legitimate business grounds for doing so. Under PDPL and European privacy laws there is a concept of “legitimate interests” as a legal justification for processing your personal data.  Our legitimate interests for processing your personal data are for us to enable you access and use of our Services, to communicate with you about our Services and to improve our Services. In order to provide you with a better service, your User Transaction, Location, Transaction Security, advertising ID information is processed.
3. It is necessary to process the personal data of the parties to the contract, provided that it is directly related to the Establishment or Performance of the Contract.
- We may need to collect and use your personal information, as applicable, to establish agreement and perform our contractual obligations to you. DeepWall is a membership-based platform. During the completion of your membership, your Identity & Contact information, Transaction Security information and Location & Language information are processed. Your financial information is processed when payment is required on your behalf.
4.
Processing of personal data in order to fulfill our legal obligations: Your name-surname and related billing information are processed during invoice creation.
