7. Which cookies do we use?
A cookie is a very small text file placed on your computer or device. We and our partners use cookies and similar technologies to provide and personalize our Services, analyze their use, target ads and prevent fraud. You can disable cookies in your browser settings, but in this case some parts of our Services may not work properly.
8. What ads do we show on our Services?
The advertisements you see displayed on our Services are provided on behalf of certain third-party advertising companies. No information that identifies you, such as your name, address, e-mail address or telephone number, is used to provide these advertisements. In order to display the advertisements that are most relevant to you, these third-party advertisers may place a cookie on your browser or use a cookie placed in this way. This cookie does not collect personal information about you or is not linked to personally identifiable information about you. By using our services, you consent to the use of such third-party cookies for these purposes.
9. What measures do we take to keep your personal data safe?
The security of your personal information is very important to us. That's why we use HTTPS where appropriate to help keep information about you secure. However, it cannot be guaranteed that information transmitted over the Internet is completely secure.
We do our best to keep the information you disclose to us secure. However, we cannot guarantee the security of the information you submit to us, and you do so at your own risk. By using our services, you accept the risks associated with providing information over the internet and you will not hold us responsible for any breach of security.
10. How long do we keep your personal information?
Unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law, your personal information will only be provided for as long as it is reasonably necessary to fulfill the purposes set forth in this Privacy and PDP Text and for our legitimate interests such as complying with legal obligations, resolving disputes, and fulfilling our contracts. we will hold. For example, we will periodically disable credentials of unused accounts and review our datasets on a regular basis.
11. Do we transfer your personal information outside of your country of residence?
Our services are global in nature and your personal information may be transferred and processed in countries other than your country of residence in accordance with your express consent. These countries may have data protection laws that differ from the laws of your own country. We take all measures to provide adequate and appropriate measures to protect your data as described in the Privacy and PDP Text. Appropriate safeguards available to our business partners include standard contractual clauses approved by the EU Commission and Privacy Protection certification if transferred to the USA.
12. Your personal data rights and ways to contact us
You have certain rights under current data protection legislation, including the right to request a copy of the personal information we hold about you, if you request it from us in writing.
Right of access: your right to request copies of your personal information from us;
Right to rectification: your right to request that we correct your personal information if it is inaccurate or incomplete;
Right to delete: your right to request the deletion and removal of your personal information from our systems;
The right to restrict the use of your information: your right to request that we “block” our use of your personal information or limit the ways we use it;
Right to data portability: your right to request that we move, copy or transfer your personal information;
Right to object: your right to object to our use of your personal information, including where we use it for our legitimate interests.
Your Rights as a Relevant Person Pursuant to Article 11 of KVKK
Your requests, questions and complaints regarding your aforementioned rights, as personal data owners, in written form and with the documents identifying your identity, together with your written petition containing your explanations about the right you want to exercise, to our Company's Maslak Mah. Buyukdere Cad. Uso Center NTV Apt. No:245 Kat:7 Sarıyer/ İSTANBUL in person, via a notary public or by registered letter with return receipt or by sending an e-mail to info@deepwall.com or support@deepwall.com, your request will be evaluated by our Company and will be sent to the fastest way possible as stipulated within the scope of PDPL. will be finalized within 30 (thirty) days. Although it is essential not to charge any fee for the requests, our Company reserves the right to charge a fee based on the fee schedule determined by the Personal Data Protection Board.
Without prejudice to the cases stipulated in Article 28 of the PDPL titled 'Exceptions', by applying to our Company; learning whether it has been processed; request information about it if it has been processed; learning the purpose of processing and whether it is used in accordance with its purpose; knowing the third parties to whom it has been transferred in the country or abroad; requesting notification of transactions made by third parties to which it has been transferred; requesting their correction if they are incomplete or incorrectly processed; requesting its deletion or destruction in the event that the reasons requiring its processing disappear; requesting the notification of the transactions made to the third parties to whom your personal data has been transferred; Within the scope of PDPL, we inform you that you have the right to object to the emergence of a result against you by analyzing it exclusively through automatic systems and to demand the compensation of the damage in case you suffer damage due to the processing in violation of the PDPL, as a 'Data Controller'.
Changes to this Privacy and PDP Text
We reserve the right to amend or modify this Privacy and PDP Text at any time and any changes will be published on our Services.  The date of the most recent revision will appear on this page.  If we make significant changes to this policy, we may also notify you by other means such as sending an email.  Where required by law we will obtain your consent to make these changes.  If you do not agree with any changes, please do not continue to use our Services.
Exclusive rights to EEA and UK users
Individuals subject to European data protection laws may have data subject rights in relation to the personal data we hold on them. This in itself may be subject to limitations and/or restrictions. If you are in the EEA (European Economic Area), please contact us to exercise your rights.
Access to Data
If requested, we will confirm whether we are processing your personal data and, if so, we will provide you with a copy of this personal data along with other relevant information.
Restricting the processing of personal data
You can ask us to restrict or 'block' the processing of personal information in certain of your data, for example you may object to the accuracy or processing of the data. We will notify you before removing any restrictions on processing. If we share your personal data with others, we will notify them of the restriction where possible. If requested and if this is possible and legal, we will let you know with whom we share it or share your personal data so you can contact us directly if necessary.
Objections
Your rights:
You can ask us to stop processing your personal data at any time. If we rely on a legitimate interest to process your personal data, there should be no problem as long as we demonstrate essential legitimate grounds for processing;
You can object to the processing of your data for marketing purposes at any time. This can be done via 'unsubscribe' in our marketing emails; and
refuse to receive service notifications via e-mail.
You can opt out of giving us further access to your location data at any time by emailing info@deepwall.com or support@deepwall.com.
Withdrawal of approval
Although we rely on your consent to process your personal data, you have the right to withdraw this consent at any time. Please be aware that this does not change the way we process your data before we receive notification of your request to withdraw your consent.
Appearance and correction of data
You have the right to have incomplete or inaccurate personal data rectified or completed. If your personal data is shared with others, we will also notify them of the correction.
Deletion of data
You have the right to refuse to use our Website / product and in certain circumstances you may request that we delete or remove your personal data. If we share your data with others, we will again notify them of changes where possible. If requested, and wherever possible and legal, we will also inform you with whom we share your personal data so that you can contact them directly if necessary.
Data retention
We will retain your personal data until you decide to delete your account (on request) or as required by law or for legitimate business purposes (tax, legal, accounting, fraud or abuse prevention and/or other purposes). This data can be retained even after an account is deleted.
Upon expiration of the applicable retention period, we will securely destroy your personal data in accordance with applicable laws and regulations. In some cases, we may anonymize your personal data so that it can no longer be associated with you. In this case, such data is no longer considered personal.
If you agree to receive marketing communications, we will retain your data until you unsubscribe; this is possible with the 'unsubscribe' button at the end of our marketing emails. Additional methods for unsubscribing may be added in the future.
Data portability
You have the right to receive from us your personal data that you have agreed to provide to us or that are necessary to us in connection with our contract with you. We will provide your personal data in a structured, commonly used and computer-readable format.
Making a complaint to the data protection authority
Please contact us if you have questions about our privacy practices, including our personal data processing practice or our privacy practices. Note that we may need to ask you for more information to verify your identity before responding to any request.
Exclusive rights of users resident in California
If you are a valid California resident, the California Consumer Privacy Act ('CCPA') gives you specific rights regarding our collection and use of your personal information. You have the following rights under the CCPA:
The right to request clarification regarding certain information about our collection and use of your personal information in the last 12 months.
List of categories of personal information collected and disclosed about consumers “What personal information do we collect?” In the section 'Who do we share your personal information with?'
Please contact us to request data portability.
You have the right to request the deletion of the personal information we collect from you.
